        "orario": "10:57",
        "timestamp": 1773482248,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. US military bombs military sites on Kharg island, Iranian media reports no damage Middle East Issued on: 14/03/2026 - 10:57 President Donald Trump said the US destroyed military sites on an island vital to Iran’s oil network and warned that its oil infrastructure could be next if Iran continues to interfere with the passage of ships through the Strait of Hormuz. Iran's Fars news agency, citing sources on Kharg Island, said there had been no damage to oil facilities and that only military targets had been destroyed by the US strikes. Story by Peter O'Brien and Lou Kisiela. War in the Middle East: A sailor stranded in the Gulf fears for his safety 13/03/2026 Middle East As 800,000 flee, half of Lebanon lives in war zones without markets, supplies or healthcare 13/03/2026 Middle East Lebanon’s Mission Impossible: Could US and Israeli pressure to disarm Hezbollah lead to civil war? 13/03/2026 Middle East Strait of Hormuz: Iran leverages control of a critical chokepoint in the global oil trade 13/03/2026 Middle East 'Mental, subjective impact': Iran taking on 'American might' with cyberterrorism 13/03/2026 Middle East Israel widens Lebanon bombing campaign to target north and central Beirut 13/03/2026 On the ground Middle East Netanyahu says new Iran leader 'can't show his face in public' 12/03/2026 Middle East Iran to allow India-flagged tankers to pass through Strait of Hormuz (reports) 12/03/2026 Middle East US Democrats call for 'swift investigation' into strike on Iranian school 12/03/2026 Middle East"
